This paper focuses on the simulation and optimization of shared autonomous electric vehicle (SAEV) services, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and optimization techniques. The paper also discusses the impact of charging infrastructure on SAEV service performance, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper uses an agent-based simulation approach to model the SAEV service, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the importance of data analysis and optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
